BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gcC_cQ091tHdQmzwjk4CJ
SUMMARY:Root in Recipriocity: Tend Together
DTSTAMP:20260306T004520Z
DTSTART:20260307T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Seward Park. \\nCaring 
	for the land that cares for us. \\nThe land around us has been scarred by 
	pollution\\\, carved over by development\\\, and fragmented by development
	 expansion. To live in reciprocity means to give back\\\, to tend\\\, and 
	to restore what has been lost. Are you in good relations with the land? By
	 stepping into this work\\\, we have the chance to give back\\\, repair ha
	bitats\\\, support native wildlife\\\, and strengthen our connection to th
	e Land. Restoration is our way of returning care to the land that has long
	 sustained us. \\nJoin us at Seward Park Audubon Center for Root in Recipr
	ocity: Tend Together. Together\\\, we’ll be engaging in either the removal
	 and repurpose of introduced species\\\, plant native flora\\\, and restor
	e habitats that sustain birds\\\, pollinators\\\, and the broader ecosyste
	m. All tools\\\, guidance\\\, and materials are provided\\\, just bring yo
	ur curiosity\\\, care\\\, and willingness to get your hands in the soil. \
	\nRegister\n\nhttps://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/root-in-recipri
	ocity-tend-together-3/\n\nFrom The Seattle Parks Foundation
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/root-in-recipriocity-tend-
	together-3/
LOCATION:Seward Park\\\, 5900 Lake Washington Blvd S\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\,
	 United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-parks-foundation
CATEGORIES:The Seattle Parks Foundation
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
