BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aFRM7Twer-6KqLbuccHKI
SUMMARY:Presidential Speaker Series: Eboo Patel
DTSTAMP:20260306T004520Z
DTSTART:20260312T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Presidential Speaker Series\, introduced in 2023\, centers 
	on freedom of speech\, viewpoint diversity\, and campus dialogue. Open to 
	all members of the Seattle University community\, the series features nati
	onally recognized scholars and thought leaders.\n\n \n\nJoin us for the ne
	xt Fireside Chat on Wednesday\, March 11\,  with Eboo Patel\, Founder and 
	President of Interfaith America\, the nation’s leading interfaith organiza
	tion co-hosted by Blue City Blues podcast hosts David Hyde and Sandeep Kau
	shik\n\n \n\nEboo Patel\n\nEboo Patel is a civic leader\, speaker\, and au
	thor advancing the notion that diversity is a treasure and cooperation acr
	oss our difference is the key for everybody to thrive. Recognized as “one 
	of America’s best leaders” by U.S. News and World Report\, he is the Found
	er and President of Interfaith America\, the nation’s leading interfaith o
	rganization.\n\nUnder Eboo’s leadership\, Interfaith America has grown int
	o a $20 million-per-year organization that partners with governments\, uni
	versities\, businesses\, and civic organizations to transform faith into a
	 bridge of cooperation rather than a barrier of division.\n\nEboo’s impact
	 extends to serving on President Obama’s Inaugural Faith Council\, deliver
	ing hundreds of keynote addresses\, and authoring five influential books\,
	 including We Need to Build: Field Notes for Diverse Democracy. A Rhodes S
	cholar and Ashoka Fellow\, Eboo earned a doctorate in the sociology of rel
	igion from Oxford University.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/det
	ails/presidential-speaker-series-eboo-patel/17592460/2026-03-11T00\n\nFrom
	 SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/presidential-speaker-seri
	es-eboo-patel/17592460/2026-03-11T00
LOCATION:Pigott Building\, Pigott Auditorium (PIGT 104)\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
